                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_farsylyvzag" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>farsylyvzag</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>farsi ævzag</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>селезенка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>spleen</q></tr></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Буквально „язык (%iyvzag%i) на боку (%ifarsyl%i)“; см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fars"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yvzag"/>. По связи с %ifars%i ‘бок’ ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-vanəza</w> <gloss><q>селезенка</q></gloss></mentioned>, от <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-va(ra)</w> <gloss><q>бок</q></gloss></mentioned> („то, что прикреплено к боку“).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Literally ‘a tongue (%iyvzag%i) on the side (%ifarsyl%i)’; see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fars"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yvzag"/>. In connection to %ifars%i ‘side’ cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-vanəza</w> <gloss><q>spleen</q></gloss></mentioned>, from <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-va(ra)</w> <gloss><q>side</q></gloss></mentioned> (‘thing that is attached to the side’).</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>